# Claude Code — local-only tooling, secrets, and per-machine state.
# Decision (2026-04-26, Trello card #2): gitignore entire .claude/ rather
# than tracking it selectively. Solo dev, no team sharing concern. Contents:
#   - settings.local.json: contains secrets (Trello token, etc.)
#   - worktrees/: per-machine isolated agent working copies
#   - any hooks/agents/skills added later stay personal until explicitly shared
# If ever sharing tooling with a team, lift this rule selectively.
.claude/

# MCP server config — env block holds secrets (e.g. Trello API token).
# Track template separately as .mcp.json.example if/when sharing is needed.
.mcp.json